1.title: SXSW: Part 1

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

1.plot: Follow the Young Hollywood crew's adventures as they travel to Austin, Texas, to explore the Music Capital of the World during the South By Southwest Music & Arts Festival, featuring run-ins with stars like Danish band Lukas Graham, DJ duo The Chainsmokers, songstress Daya, funk icon George Clinton, and celebrity chef Rachael Ray.

2.title: SXSW: Part 2

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

2.plot: The Young Hollywood crew wraps up their adventures in Austin, Texas, at the South By Southwest Music & Arts Festival with a pedicab tour of downtown Austin with Travis Mills, a surprise lunch with Lil Dicky, late-night partying with K Camp, and a hotel soiree with Yo Gotti.

3.title: Coachella: Part 1

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

3.plot: "Travel to Coachella, Weekend One, with the YH Crew as they ride ATVs with Ross Lynch and his pop rock band R5 and take a one-of-a-kind Palm Springs boat ride with Laura Marano before the festival kicks off."

4.title: Coachella: Part 2

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

4.plot: "The YH crew continues to vibe out at Weekend One of Coachella with pop star Bonnie McKee, while the band Phases takes the crew to the hottest day party at Coachella, and Disney star Olivia Holt gets stranded on a boat."

5.title: Electric Daisy Carnival: Part 1

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

5.plot: "The YH crew heads to Las Vegas for the 20th annual Electric Daisy Carnival (EDC) and immerse themselves fully in "PLUR" culture. They also hang out with the top DJs in the world, including Laidback Luke, who schools the crew on proper rave gear, Oliver Heldens, who teaches them his signature shuffle move, and Hardwell, who reveals what to expect from the carnival."

6.title: Electric Daisy Carnival Part 2

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

6.plot: "The YH's crew adventures in Las Vegas continue at the Electric Daisy Carnival (EDC), where DJ Martin Garrix teases the opening intro to his set, Armin van Buuren joins the crew for lunch at Mr Chow, the legendary Paul Oakenfold shares some of his Perfectomundo tequila, plus the crew crosses some items off their EDC bucket list."

7.title: Comic-Con: Part 1

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

7.plot: "The Young Hollywood crew heads to San Diego and the Mecca of geekdom, Comic-Con, where they run into "Shannara Chronicles" star and MTV Fandom Awards host Austin Butler, hang out at Nerd HQ with Zachary Levi, chat with stars of "The Vampire Diaries" on the press line, and team up with the cast of Nickelodeon's "All That" to take the ultimate "Double Dare" challenge."

8.title: Comic-Con: Part 2

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

8.plot: "The Young Hollywood crew's nerd quest continues at San Diego Comic-Con with a little mechanical bull-riding and sumo wrestling at the (Impractical) Jokers Block Party, a tour of the Viceland bus, run-ins with countless cosplayers, and interviews with the casts of "Time After Time", "Frequency", and "The 100"."

9.title: Life Is Beautiful: Part 1

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

9.plot: "Join the Young Hollywood crew in Las Vegas for a transcendent weekend at the Life is Beautiful music festival, including a tour of the space from founders Ryan Doherty and Justin Weniger, a golf cart ride with multi-instrumentalist Jack Garratt, plus hanging out with The Temper Trap, Dirty J and Duddy B of Dirty Heads, and the legend himself Mike Tyson."

10.title: Life Is Beautiful: Part 2

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

10.plot: "The Young Hollywood crew's continuing adventures at the Life is Beautiful festival in Las Vegas include: getting pumped backstage with Swedish EDM duo Galantis; T-shirt shopping with Kele Okereke of indie rock band Bloc Party; touring the grounds with singer-songwriter Pete Yorn; sampling Coolhaus's special ice cream sandwich; getting their hair styled by soul trap musician Bishop Briggs; and having dinner with deep house DJ Duke Dumont."

11.title: SXSW REDUX: Part 1

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

11.plot: The Young Hollywood Crew makes its triumphant return to Austin, Texas, for the South By Southwest Festival. This year's adventures include: escorting Australian singer-songwriter Starley to her gig at the MTV Woodies; getting on A$AP Ferg's level; running through the streets of Austin to catch up with Desiigner after his performance at the UMG Showcase; and a tour of the meat pit at Stubb's Bar-B-Q followed by lunch with electropop duo Marian Hill.

12.title: SXSW REDUX: Part 2

episode of.title: Young Hollywood on the Go (TV Series 2016– )

12.plot: Continuing our adventures at SXSW in Austin, the YH Crew greets fans and munches on egg rolls with alt-rock duo POWERS, climbs atop the Viceland bus to hang out with hip-hop producer Mike Will, takes a relaxing boat trip with Norwegian DJ Matoma, and riding in a pedicab and sharing some ice cream with Norwegian singer/songwriter Sigrid.

imdb.plot outline: Ever wonder how a celebrity experiences some of the world's biggest events? We give you the VIP Access you've been waiting for to the year's most buzzed about happenings, as seen through the YH team. Whether we take your favorite celebrity ATV riding, or catch up with them in a hot air balloon, "Young Hollywood On The Go" gives you a chance to see the person behind the "celebrity" in a laid back, intimate atmosphere.
